<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101043799779558></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101043799779558><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=101043799779558>RE: Wiz. armor</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=101043799779558#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126085><span id=Scholar>The Honorable MentalSword</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>43 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 7th 4:13 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Silk armor is probably the cheapest/easiest thing for you to seek out as far as armor goes.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is often a heavily practiced item for mid-skill tailors, and as such, practicing tailors may make the armor for you free.  You just collect the silk and buy the patterns (a couple of PP each, I believe).  You may loose a few now and then with failures, but still, it is not a bad deal.<br><br>For jewelry, most of the good stuff is very expensive (hundreds of plat), but you should be able to pick up a crafted Silver Engagement ring with +2 INT for a couple of PP.<br><br>Depending on your race and where you hunt, you might be best to just pick up these two skills for yourself.  The rings are a pretty easy thing to make and don't require a real high skill (can be done with less than 20), and the components are not expensive.  You'll have to practice tailoring a while before you can do silk, but it might be worth it to you if you can't find a tailor to work with.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
