<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100949230948151></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100949230948151><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100949230948151>RE: Wizard Problems</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=100949230948151#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126085><span id=Scholar>The Honorable MentalSword</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>43 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 27th 5:31 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm afraid there is no &quot;cure-all&quot; for your problem (short of the obvious twinking).&nbsp;&nbsp;What you are experiencing is part of the challenge of being a Wizard.  I can only offer a few bits of advice:<br><br>First, when soloing, try root, nuke, nuke, root.  Using this strategy you should be able to get those white and blue cents down to just a few HP.  Enough that you can club them to death to finish them off.  Be sure you stay on orc hill though, as the times when root wears off early, you will probably need to pull to the guards.<br><br>Secondly, DON'T SOLO!  Get in a group.  You'll find leveling much easier that way.  Especially if you can take a full group into CB.  Then, after you hit 12, go to Steamfont and camp behind the windmills.  You'll get good loot and exp here for your level.<br><br>I wouldn't expect much in the way of plus int/mana items for a while.  The good ones are tough to come by.  The truth is though that you can get by fine, equipped just as you are, with a good group.  You may, though, seek out some young jewelers and tailors as they may have affordable wares for you.  There is a silver engagement ring which is fairly simple to make that will provide +2 int each.  Also the silk armor made by tailors is only a mid-level tailoring item and should not be too expensive to acquire.  Since it is a major training item for advanced tailoring you should be able to find someone working on tailoring who will craft the armor for free (you buy the patterns and collect the spider silk), they get the benefit of the training.<br><br>So to sum it up, you are really in ok shape for your level.  Concentrate on developing your playing strategies and group skills and you'll do fine.  =)<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
