<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10086042991891></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10086042991891><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10086042991891>RE: Erudite??</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10086042991891#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126085><span id=Scholar>The Honorable MentalSword</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>43 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 17th 10:51 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Being an Erudite can certainly have its advantages for any of the heavy caster classes.&nbsp;&nbsp;But these advantages come at the price of a more dangerous beginning for your character.<br><br>If you are would like your beginning levels to be easier, I would suggest creating a High Elf Wizard.  Felwithe is a safe and easy city to navigate and it contains nearly everything a Wizard will need up to level 20 and much of what you'll need beyond.  Greater Faydark is a great newbie zone which will easily sustain you to level 7 or 8, at which point you can travel to either of two adjacent zones (Butcher Block or Crush Bone) for easy advancement from 8 to 12 or 13.  After that I recommend the quick hop through LFay to Steamfont.  You'll find excellent hunting back behind the windmills, a little before the mino caves.  This should get you well to 16 or so after which youre set to do what you like!  Reference www.eqatlas.com for all of the zone maps.<br><br>If youre still set on an Erudite though, the only advice I can offer is to GROUP GROUP GROUP!!!<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Rivious<br>Wizard of the 18th Circle<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
