	   <tr><td colspan=2>It would seem some of us wizards are concerned about the use of a familar. Not having the lvl29 I will not attempt to speak on that. I do however, have the lvl 49.<br><br>Traditionaly familars are always trouble makers. They have also always provided the wizard with increased abilities.<br><br>My uses of &quot;flappy&quot;: XP grind groups, soloing, doing tradeskills. 1 extra tick of mana is better than none. Seeing invis, how invaluable can that be on a PvP server? +15 on all saves. Well, those shrooms in various luclin zones cast, some mobs are casting Ice Comet. +15 extra on my cold save is very nice.<br><br>When not to use flappy: any raid against mob's that cast AoE's (dragons). He will die fast. since you are &quot;connected&quot; to the familar by him being a living buff, it makes sence that you would be effected in a negative way at his death. you can click him off with no mana penalty.<br><br>Flappy has a place in the wizards life, you just need to know where and when to use him (like all of our spells).<br><br>After several TL's my mana pool is low. Having flappy regen me while I stand is awesome. I still hear &quot;1 tick is not worth it&quot;. Ok, maybe not but now lets add the epics 3 ticks, the 7th shawls's 1 tick, manaskin, AA mental clarity ticks and guess what? youre a mana regening fool 'cause they all add up! then add bard song and/or c/c2/boon? WOW!<br><br>you don't have to like or use flappy but atleast give him a try. I cast the 49 with rare fizzles at a 187 conjur spell skill.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
